<a>
    <!--<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ecd.css" /><body style="height:2000px;"><div id="topAnchor"></div><a href="#topAnchor" style="position:fixed;right:0;bottom:0">回到顶部</a></body><div class="phrase"><span class="l">a bit of</span><div class="se2"><span class="df">有几分…(特征)的人(或地方、局面)</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">He is <span class="i">a bit of</span> a coward.</span>他多少有几分怯懦。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">The place is <span class="i">a bit of</span> a backwater.</span>这地方多少有点闭塞。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">微不足道的一个</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">We are having <span class="i">a bit of</span> a party next week.</span>下星期我们准备请几位客人小聚一次。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">相当数量的,相当规模的;相当不小的一个(或一次)</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">The humour of it takes <span class="i">a bit of</span> finding.</span>其中的幽默非细细体会不可。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">I must have <span class="i">a bit of</span> a chat with you — this very night.</span>我一定得同你好好谈一谈——今夜就谈。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">He had <span class="i">a bit of</span> a shock.</span>他受到极大的震惊。</div></div></div><div class="mainentry">Main Entry: <a class="mainentrylink" href="entry://bit">bit</a></div>-->
    <!--<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ecd.css" /><body style="height:2000px;"><div id="topAnchor"></div><a href="#topAnchor" style="position:fixed;right:0;bottom:0">回到顶部</a></body><div class="phrase"><span class="l">a hue and cry</span><div class="se2"><span class="df">(呼唤众人追捕逃犯或嫌疑犯等的)喊捉声,捉拿声(旧时英国法律准许追捕者大声呼唤,听见呼喊者有义务参加追捕)</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">“Stop thief,” cried John as he ran. Others joined him, and soon there was <span class="i">a hue and cry</span>.</span>“捉贼,”约翰边奔边喊。众人跟着他喊,于是刹那间响起一片喊捉声。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">高声喊捉的追捕;通缉令</span></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">大声抗议;大声报警</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">They raised <span class="i">a hue and cry</span> against the new rule.</span>他们大声提出抗议,反对新规定。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">喧嚷;骚动</span></div></div><div class="mainentry">Main Entry: <a class="mainentrylink" href="entry://hue">hue</a></div>-->
    <!--<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ecd.css" /><body style="height:2000px;"><div id="topAnchor"></div><a href="#topAnchor" style="position:fixed;right:0;bottom:0">回到顶部</a></body><div class="phrase"><span class="l">allow me</span><div class="se2"><span class="df">允许我…</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex"><span class="i">Allow me</span> to introduce Mrs. Lincoln to you.</span>允许我向你介绍林肯夫人。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">口语中用于指出别人错误等场合,相当于 pardon me</span><span class="df">对不起</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex"><span class="i">Allow me</span>, that pencil is mine.</span>对不起,那支铅笔是我的。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">口语中用于自告奋勇做某事等场合</span><span class="df">让我来</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">A: Oh, my string bag caught on your button. B:<span class="i">Allow me</span>, madam. Now it’s all right.</span>甲:唷,我的网线袋缠在你钮扣上了。乙:让我来,太太。行了,解开了。</div></div></div><div class="mainentry">Main Entry: <a class="mainentrylink" href="entry://allow">allow</a></div>-->
    <!--<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ecd.css" /><body style="height:2000px;"><div id="topAnchor"></div><a href="#topAnchor" style="position:fixed;right:0;bottom:0">回到顶部</a></body><div class="phrase"><span class="l">all right</span><div class="se2"><span class="df">安全的;安然无恙的;(健康)良好的</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">I was ill for a week, but I’m <span class="i">all right</span> now.</span>我病了一个星期,但现在好了。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">正确的,对的</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">The answers were <span class="i">all right</span>.</span>回答正确无误。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">Am I <span class="i">all right</span> for Bristol on this road?</span>我去布里斯托尔走这条路对吗?</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">表示同意</span><span class="df">好,行,可以</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">A: Will you meet me at ten o’clock? B: <span class="i">All right</span>.</span>甲:你能在十点钟同我碰头吗? 乙:行。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">表示讥讽、不耐烦、威胁等</span><span class="df">好啊;没关系</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex"><span class="i">All right</span>! Then we’ll see who is master here.</span>好啊!等着瞧,看这儿究竟谁说了算。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">令人满意的;适宜的;不错的</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">His performance was <span class="i">all right</span>.</span>他的表现还令人满意。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">Is the arrangement <span class="i">all right</span> with you?</span>这样安排对你方便吗?</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">Will the 3.15 train be all <span class="i">right</span> for you?</span>3点15分的那班火车对你合适吗?</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">令人满意地;还好</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">The engine seemed to be working <span class="i">all right</span>.</span>发动机似乎运转得还好。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">用以加强语气</span><span class="df">确实,无疑地</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">She called herself Hopkins; but it was Mrs. Draper <span class="i">all right</span>.</span>她说她自己是霍普金斯,但其实就是德雷珀夫人。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="df">没有什么,不要紧</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">It’s <span class="i">all right</span>; there’s no harm done.</span>不要紧,没伤着。</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">Is it <span class="i">all right</span> to you if I catch the 3.15 train?</span>如果我乘3点15分那班火车,对你没有什么妨碍吧?</div><div class="eg"><span class="ex">She was <span class="i">all right</span> about it.</span>她对此并不介意。</div></div><div class="se2"><span class="gg">用作连接叙述中的两个阶段</span><span class="df">好</span><div class="eg"><span class="ex">You have followed the explanation so far? <span class="i">All right</span>, now we come to the second stage.</span>到此为止你们听得懂我的解释吧?那好,现在让我们讨论第二阶段的内容。</div></div></div><div class="mainentry">Main Entry: <a class="mainentrylink" href="entry://all">all</a></div>-->
